#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Innledning"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Welcome to &kdesu;! &kdesu; is a graphical front end for the &UNIX; "
"<command>su</command> command for the K Desktop Environment. It allows you "
"to run a program as different user by supplying the password for that user. "
"&kdesu; is an unprivileged program; it uses the system's <command>su</"
"command>."
msgstr ""
"Dette er &kdesu;!  &kdesu; er et grafisk grensesnitt for &UNIX;-kommandoen "
"<command>su</command> for skrivebordsmiljøet KDE. Med det kan du kjøre et "
"program som en annen bruker ved å oppgi den brukerens passord. &kdesu; er et "
"ikke-privilegert program, det bruker systemets <command>su</command>-"
"kommando."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdesu; has one additional feature: it can remember passwords for you. If "
"you are using this feature, you only need to enter the password once for "
"each command. See <xref linkend=\"sec-password-keeping\"/> for more "
"information on this and a security analysis."
msgstr ""
"&kdesu; har en funksjon til: det kan huske passord for deg. Hvis du bruker "
"denne funksjonen trenger du bare oppgi passordet én gang for hver kommando. "
"For mer om dette og en sikkerhetsanalyse, se i <xref linkend=\"sec-password-"
"keeping\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This program is meant to be started from the command line or from <filename>."
"desktop</filename> files. Although it asks for the <systemitem class="
"\"username\">root</systemitem> password using a &GUI; dialog, I consider it "
"to be more of a command line &lt;-&gt; &GUI; glue instead of a pure &GUI; "
"program."
msgstr ""
"Dette programmet er ment å startes fra kommandolinja eller fra <filename>."
"desktop</filename>-filer. Selv om det ber om <systemitem class=\"username"
"\">root</systemitem>-passordet med en &GUI;-dialog, så ser jeg på det mer "
"som et lim-program mellom kommandolinja &lt;-&gt; og et &GUI;. i stedet for "
"et rent &GUI;-program."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since <command>kdesu</command> is no longer installed in <userinput> $(kf5-"
"config --prefix)</userinput>/bin but in <userinput>kf5-config --path "
"libexec</userinput> and therefore not in your <envar>Path</envar>, you have "
"to use <userinput>$(kf5-config --path libexec)<command>kdesu</command></"
"userinput> to launch <command>kdesu</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &kdesu;"
msgstr "Bruke &kdesu;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usage of &kdesu; is easy. The syntax is like this:"
msgstr "Det er lett å bruke &kdesu;. Syntaksen er slik:"

#. Tag: cmdsynopsis
#: index.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdesu</command> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-c</option> "
"<replaceable> command</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-"
"d</option></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-f</option> <replaceable> "
"file</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-i</option> "
"<replaceable> icon name</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-"
"n</option></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-p</option> <replaceable> "
"priority</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-r</option></"
"group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-s</option></group> <group choice=\"opt"
"\"><option>-t</option></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-u</option> "
"<replaceable> user</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>--"
"noignorebutton</option></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>--attach</"
"option> <replaceable> winid</replaceable></group>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdesu</command> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-c</option> "
"<replaceable> kommando</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-"
"d</option></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-f</option> <replaceable> "
"file</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-i</option> "
"<replaceable> icon name</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-"
"n</option></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-p</option> <replaceable> "
"priority</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-r</option></"
"group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-s</option></group> <group choice=\"opt"
"\"><option>-t</option></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>-u</option> "
"<replaceable> user</replaceable></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>--"
"noignorebutton</option></group> <group choice=\"opt\"><option>--attach</"
"option> <replaceable> winid</replaceable></group>"

#. Tag: cmdsynopsis
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdesu</command> <arg choice=\"opt\">&kde; Generic Options</arg> "
"<arg choice=\"opt\">&Qt; Generic Options</arg>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdesu</command> <arg choice=\"opt\">&kde;-spesifikke valg</arg> "
"<arg choice=\"opt\">&Qt;-spesifikke valg</arg>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "The command line options are explained below."
msgstr "Kommandolinjevalgene forklares nedenfor."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "-c <replaceable>command</replaceable>"
msgstr "-c <replaceable>kommando</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This specifies the command to run as root. It has to be passed in one "
"argument. So if, for example, you want to start a new file manager, you "
"would enter at the prompt: <userinput>$(kf5-config --path "
"libexec)<command>kdesu <option>-c <replaceable> &dolphin;</replaceable></"
"option></command></userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-d</option>"
msgstr "<option>-d</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show debug information."
msgstr "Vis feilsøkingsinformasjon"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "-f <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "-f <replaceable>fil</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option allow efficient use of &kdesu; in <filename>.desktop</filename> "
"files. It tells &kdesu; to examine the file specified by <parameter>file</"
"parameter>. If this file is writable by the current user, &kdesu; will "
"execute the command as the current user. If it is not writable, the command "
"is executed as user <parameter>user</parameter> (defaults to root)."
msgstr ""
"Dette valget fører til effektiv bruk av &kdesu; i <filename>.desktop</"
"filename>-filer. det får &kdesu; til  undersøke fila <parameter>fil</"
"parameter>, og hvis gjelddende bruker kan skrive til den, så kjører &kdesu; "
"kommandoen som gjeldende bruker. Hvis fila ikke er skrivbar, så kjøres "
"kommandoen som bruker <parameter>bruker</parameter> (standard er root)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<parameter>file</parameter> is evaluated like this: if <parameter>file</"
"parameter> starts with a <literal>/</literal>, it is taken as an absolute "
"filename. Otherwise, it is taken as the name of a global &kde; configuration "
"file."
msgstr ""
"<parameter>fil</parameter> utvikles slik: hvis <parameter>fil</parameter> "
"begynner med en <literal>/</literal>, så er det et absolutt filnavn, ellers "
"blir det tatt for navnet på en global &kde; oppsettsfil."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-i</option> <replaceable>icon name</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-i</option> <replaceable>ikonnavn</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify icon to use in the password dialog. You may specify just the name, "
"without any extension."
msgstr ""
"Oppgi iklon som skal brukes i passord-dialogen. Du kan oppgi bare navnet, "
"uten etternavn."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For instance to run &konqueror; in filemanager mode and show the &konqueror; "
"icon in the password dialog:"
msgstr ""
"For eksempel: kjør &konqueror; i filbehandlermodus og vis &konqueror;-ikonet "
"i passord-dialogen:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>$(kf5-config --path libexec)<command>kdesu</command>  <option>-i "
"konqueror</option>\n"
"<option>-c \"konqueror --profile filemanagement\"</option></userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-n</option>"
msgstr "<option>-n</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not keep the password. This disables the <guilabel>keep password</"
"guilabel> checkbox in the password dialog."
msgstr ""
"Ikke behold passordet. Dette slår av avkryssingsboksen <guilabel>Husk "
"passord</guilabel> i passord-dialogen."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-p</option> <replaceable>priority</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-p</option> <replaceable>prioritet</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set priority value. The priority is an arbitrary number between 0 and 100, "
"where 100 means highest priority, and 0 means lowest. The default is 50."
msgstr ""
"Sett prioritet. Prioriteten er et fritt valgt tall mellom 0 og 100, der 100 "
"er høyeste prioritet og 0 er laveste. Standard er 50."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-r</option>"
msgstr "<option>-r</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use realtime scheduling."
msgstr "Bruk sanntidsplanlegging."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-s</option>"
msgstr "<option>-s</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stop the kdesu daemon. See <xref linkend=\"sec-password-keeping\"/>."
msgstr "Stopp kdesu-nissen. Se <xref linkend=\"sec-password-keeping\"/>."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-t</option>"
msgstr "<option>-t</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable terminal output. This disables password keeping. This is largely for "
"debugging purposes; if you want to run a console mode app, use the standard "
"<command>su</command> instead."
msgstr ""
"Slå på utdata til terminal. Dette slår av passordlagring. Brukes for det "
"meste til feilsøking, hvis du vil bruke et konsollprogram, så bruk standard "
"<command>su</command>-kommando i stedet."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-u</option> <replaceable> user</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-u</option> <replaceable> bruker</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While the most common use for &kdesu; is to run a command as the superuser, "
"you can supply any user name and the appropriate password."
msgstr ""
"Det vanligste ved bruk av &kdesu; er å kjøre en kommando som superbruker, "
"men du kan også oppgi andre brukernavn og tilhørende passord."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "Internals"
msgstr "Internt"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid "X authentication"
msgstr "X-autentisering"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The program you execute will run under the root user id and will generally "
"have no authority to access your X display. &kdesu; gets around this by "
"adding an authentication cookie for your display to a temporary <filename>."
"Xauthority</filename> file. After the command exits, this file is removed."
msgstr ""
"Programmet du kjører vil kjøres med superbruker-id og vil vanligvis ikke ha "
"rett til å skrive på din X-skjerm. &kdesu; omgår dette ved å legge til en "
"autorisasjonskapsel for skjermen din til en midlertidig <filename>."
"Xauthority</filename>-fil. Når kommandoen avslutter, fjernes fila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you don't use X cookies, you are on your own. &kdesu; will detect this "
"and will not add a cookie but you will have to make sure that root is "
"allowed to access to your display."
msgstr ""
"Hvis du ikke bruker X-kapsler (cookies), så må du klare deg selv. &kdesu; "
"merker dette og legger ikke til en kapsel, men du må sikre at root har "
"tilgang til skjermen din."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid "Interface to <command>su</command>"
msgstr "Grensesnitt til <command>su</command>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:216
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdesu; uses the sytem's <command>su</command> for acquiring priviliges. In "
"this section, I explain the details of how &kdesu; does this."
msgstr ""
"&kdesu; bruker systemets <command>su</command>-kommando for å skaffe seg "
"privilegier. I dette avsnittet forklares det hvordan &kdesu; gjør dette."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because some <command>su</command> implementations (&ie; the one from "
"&RedHat;) don't want to read the password from <literal>stdin</literal>, "
"&kdesu; creates a pty/tty pair and executes <command>su</command> with its "
"standard filedescriptors connected to the tty."
msgstr ""
"Fordi noen <command>su</command>-versjoner (&ie; dvs. den fra &RedHat;) ikke "
"vil lese passordet fra <literal>stdin</literal>, oppretter &kdesu; et pty/"
"tty-par og kjører <command>su</command> med standard filbeskrivere koplet "
"til tty-en."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To execute the command the user selected, rather than an interactive shell, "
"&kdesu; uses the <option>-c</option> argument with <command>su</command>. "
"This argument is understood by every shell that I know of so it should work "
"portably. <command>su</command> passes this <option>-c</option> argument to "
"the target user's shell, and the shell executes the program. Example "
"command: <command>su <option>root -c <replaceable>the_program</replaceable></"
"option></command>."
msgstr ""
"For å kjøre kommandoen som brukeren valgte, i stedet for et interaktivt "
"skall, bruker &kdesu; <option>-c</option>-argumentet med <command>su</"
"command>. Alle skall jeg vet om forstår dette argumentet, så det burde "
"antakelig virke. <command>su</command> sender dette <option>-c</option>-"
"argumentet til målbrukerens skall, og skallet kjører programmet. Eksempel: "
"<command>su <option>root -c <replaceable>programmet</replaceable></option></"
"command>. "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:234
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of executing the user command directly with <command>su</command>, "
"&kdesu; executes a little stub program called <application>kdesu_stub</"
"application>. This stub (running as the target user), requests some "
"information from &kdesu; over the pty/tty channel (the stub's stdin and "
"stdout) and then executes the user's program. The information passed over "
"is: the X display, an X authentication cookie (if available), the "
"<envar>PATH</envar> and the command to run. The reason why a stub program is "
"used is that the X cookie is private information and therefore cannot be "
"passed on the command line."
msgstr ""
"I stedet for å kjøre brukerkommandoen direkte med <command>su</command>, "
"kjører &kdesu; et lite stub-program som heter <application>kdesu_stub</"
"application>. Denne stub-en kjører som målbrukeren, ber om litt informasjon "
"fra &kdesu; gjennom ptty-kanalen (stub-ens stdin og stdout) og kjører så "
"brukerprogrammet. Informasjonen som sendes over er X-skjermen, en X "
"autentiseringskapsel (hvis den finnes), miljøvariablen <envar>PATH</envar> "
"og kommandoen som skal kjøres. Grunnen til at en stub brukes er at X-"
"kapselen er privat informasjon og derfor ikke kan sendes over kommandolinja."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid "Password Checking"
msgstr "Passordkontroll"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdesu; will check the password you entered and gives an error message if it "
"is not correct. The checking is done by executing a test program: <filename>/"
"bin/true</filename>. If this succeeds, the password is assumed to be correct."
msgstr ""
"&kdesu; vil kontrollere passordet du skrev inn og gir en feilmelding hvis "
"det ikke er riktig. Kontrollen gjøres ved å kjøre et testprogram, <filename>/"
"bin/true</filename>. Hvis dette går bra blir det regnet med at passordet er "
"riktig."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:258
#, no-c-format
msgid "Password Keeping"
msgstr "Passordlagring"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For your comfort, &kdesu; implements a <quote>keep password</quote> feature. "
"If you are interested in security, you should read this paragraph."
msgstr ""
"For lettvinthets skyld har &kdesu; funksjonen <quote>Behold passord</quote>. "
"Du burde lese dette avsnittet hvis du er interessert i sikkerhet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allowing &kdesu; to remember passwords opens up a (small) security hole in "
"your system. Obviously, &kdesu; does not allow anybody but your user id to "
"use the passwords, but, if done without caution, this would lowers "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>'s security level to that of "
"a normal user (you). A hacker who breaks into your account, would get "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> access. &kdesu; tries to "
"prevent this. The security scheme it uses is, in my opinion at least, "
"reasonably safe and is explained here."
msgstr ""
"Det åpner et (lite) sikkerhetshull i systemet ditt å la &kdesu; huske "
"passord. &kdesu; lar selvsagt ingen andre enn din bruker-id bruke "
"passordene, men, hvis du er uforsiktig, kan dette senke <systemitem class="
"\"username\">roots</systemitem> sikkerhetsnivå til samme nivå som en normal "
"bruker (du). En inntrenger som bryter seg inn på brukerkontoen din ville få "
"tilgang til <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>. &kdesu; "
"forsøker å forhindre dette. Sikkerhetsopplegget det bruker er i alle fall "
"etter min mening rimelig trygt og blir forklart her."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdesu; uses a daemon, called <application>kdesud</application>. The daemon "
"listens to a &UNIX; socket in <filename>/tmp</filename> for commands. The "
"mode of the socket is 0600 so that only your user id can connect to it. If "
"password keeping is enabled, &kdesu; executes commands through this daemon. "
"It writes the command and <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>'s "
"password to the socket and the daemon executes the command using "
"<command>su</command>, as describe before. After this, the command and the "
"password are not thrown away. Instead, they are kept for a specified amount "
"of time. This is the timeout value from in the control module. If another "
"request for the same command is coming within this time period, the client "
"does not have to supply the password. To keep hackers who broke into your "
"account from stealing passwords from the daemon (for example, by attaching a "
"debugger), the daemon is installed set-group-id nogroup. This should prevent "
"all normal users (including you) from getting passwords from the "
"<application>kdesud</application> process. Also, the daemon sets the "
"<envar>DISPLAY</envar> environment variable to the value it had when it was "
"started. The only thing a hacker can do is execute an application on your "
"display."
msgstr ""
"&kdesu; bruker en daemon som heter <application>kdesud</application>. "
"Daemonen lytter etter kommandoer på en &UNIX;-sokkel i <filename>/tmp</"
"filename>. Sokkelen har modus 0600 så bare din bruker-id kan koble til den. "
"Hvis passord skal huskes kjører &kdesu; kommandoer gjennom denne daemonen, "
"det skriver kommandoen og passordet til <systemitem class=\"username\">root</"
"systemitem> til sokkelen og daemonen kjører kommandoen ved bruk av "
"<command>su</command> som beskrevet før. Deretter kastes ikke kommandoen og "
"passordet, men beholdes en bestemt tid. Dette er tiden for tidsavbrudd fra "
"kontrollmodulen. Hvis det kommer et krav om å kjøre den samme kommandoen i "
"løpet av dette tidsrommet trenger ikke klienten å oppgi  passordet. Daemonen "
"blir installert med gruppe-id nogroup for å hindre inntrengere i å stjele "
"passordet fra daemonen (for eksempel ved å koble en feilsøker til "
"prosessen). Dette burde hindre alle normale brukere (deg også) i å finne "
"passord i <application>kdesud</application>-prosessen. Dessuten setter "
"daemonen miljøvariablen <envar>DISPLAY</envar> til den verdien den hadde da "
"daemonen ble startet. Det eneste en inntrenger kan gjøre er å kjøre et "
"program på skjermen din."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:295
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One weak spot in this scheme is that the programs you execute are probably "
"not written with security in mind (like setuid <systemitem class=\"username"
"\">root</systemitem> programs). This means that they might have buffer "
"overruns or other problems and a hacker could exploit those."
msgstr ""
"Et svakt punkt i dette systemer et at programmene du kjører antakelig ikke "
"er skrevet med sikkerhet i tankene (slik som setuid <systemitem class="
"\"username\">root</systemitem>-programmer). Dette betyr at de kan a buffer-"
"overløp eller andre problemer som en inntrenger kunne utnytte."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The use of the password keeping feature is a tradeoff between security and "
"comfort. I encourage you to think it over and decide for yourself if you "
"want to use it or not."
msgstr ""
"Bruk av funksjonen Husk passord er en avveining mellom sikkerhet og "
"lettvinthet. Jeg oppfordrer deg til å tenke over saken og bestemme selv om "
"du vil bruke den eller ikke."

